2.1.1 (2016-08-17)
- cleanup tmp dirs after zip downloads
- bugfix: only add cookbook if not already added before

2.1.0 (2016-04-27)
- support wildcards in folder paths, too, e.g. for Gitlab download URLs with commit hashes ...

2.0.2 (2016-04-21)
- bugfix: do not output print_r() log message
- do not log full auth info for commercial downloads

2.0.1 (2016-04-05)
- added some logging for the download and extraction process
- improved _downloadPackage(): download urls don't have to end with .zip, the only have to contain ".zip" (e.g. for token parameters in gitlab etc.)

2.0.0 (2016-03-31)
- added parameter "preserveExisting" to install() function to allow to keep existing files in a dir

1.9.3 (2016-03-30)
- print hook messages on console, too

1.9.2 (2016-03-28)
- Bugfix: we need to update() after un-/install

1.9.1 (2016-03-28)
- added support to search for license type, e.g. "mit", "gnu" or "commercial"

1.9.0 (2016-03-27)
- support for commercial packages via "auth/<vendor>.json" files, supporting basic, token or header auth

1.8.6 (2016-03-24)
- no default console spamming

1.8.5 (2016-03-07)
- Auto-guessing of IOLY_SYSTEM_BASE path and IOLY_SYSTEM_VERSION (at least for OXID)

